@REMARK -----------------------------------
@REMARK ---   Einführung / Übersicht	---
@REMARK -----------------------------------
@NODE "INTRO_WHATIS" "About AssignList"

Use AssignList to execute as many assigns as you want at
@{" boot-time " LINK "USE_START"} by one single call.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "INTRO_SYSREQ" "Requirements"

AssignList requires at least OS 2.04 or higher and @{" MUI " LINK "MUI_README"}
version 3.1 or higher if the GUI should be used.

To call AssignList at @{" boot-time " LINK "USE_START"} only @{B}dos.library@{UB} version 37
or higher is required.

Any 680x0 cpu is supported.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "INTRO_INSTALL" "How to install AssignList ?"

Just double-click on that installer-icon in the drawer @{B}Install@{UB}
in your preferred langnguage.

All files will be copied and your @{" user-startup" LINK "USE_START"} file
will be modified.
@ENDNODE

@REMARK -----------------------------------
@REMARK ---	Benutzung		---
@REMARK -----------------------------------
@NODE "USE_START" "Getting started"
There are two ways to start AssignList:

    @{B}1. From Shell or within your user-startup file:@{UB}

        - Just type "AssignList" in your shell window or call it
          from within your user-startup and AssignList will start.
          Some arguments are supported:

            * @{B}HELP@{UB} or @{B}?@{UB}
              Prints usage.

            * @{B}<Filename>@{UB}
              The file <filename> will be loaded automatically.

            * @{B}<Filename> USE@{UB}
              The file <filename> will be loaded, all contained
              @{" assign definitions " LINK "FILE_FORMAT" will be executed
              and afterwards AssignList terminates.
              For this @{" MUI " LINK "MUI_README"} is not required.
              Also this is the standard configuration if you chose
              to modify your user-startup file on @{" installation " LINK "INTRO_INSTALL"}.

    @{B}1. From workbench:@{UB}

        - Simply double-click on the AssignList-icon. You may put
          AssignList in the @{B}WBStartup-drawer@{UB} as well.
          Some tooltypes are supported:

            * @{B}DONOTWAIT@{UB}
              If AssignList is installed in the @{B}WBStartup-drawer@{UB} tell
              the system not to wait for AssignList to terminate.

            * @{B}CX_POPKEY=<Keys>@{UB}
              Defines a sequence of keys to pop up the main window
              if AssignList was iconified.

            * @{B}CX_POPUP=<YES|NO>@{UB}
              Open the @{" main window " LINK "USE_WINDOW"} or show an icon on
              the workbench screen only.

            * @{B}FILE=@{UB}
              Load file specified after "=" automatically.

            * @{B}MAKEICONS=<YES|NO>@{UB}
              Create an icon automatically when saving a definition
              file. A double-click on a created icon would start
              AssignList and load the attached file.
              (See also @{" menu item " LINK "USE_MENU"} "Create icon".)
@ENDNODE

@NODE "USE_WINDOW" "Main window"
The main window has the following structure:


  ·-----------------------------------------------------·
  |							|
  |							|
  |          @{" List of all definied assigns " LINK "BUTT_LISTVIEW"}		|
  |							|
  |							|
  | ---------------------------------------------------	|
  |    @{"   Assign:                      " LINK "BUTT_ASSIGN"}    Mode		|
  |    @{"       to:                      " LINK "BUTT_TO"}@{" assign-modes " LINK "BUTT_MODUS"}	|
  | ---------------------------------------------------	|
  |    @{"Execute... " LINK "BUTT_DO"}    @{"     Add      " LINK "BUTT_ADD"}     @{"  Delete  " LINK "BUTT_DEL"}	|
  | ---------------------------------------------------	|
  |    @{"   Save    " LINK "BUTT_SAVE"}    @{"  Save & End  " LINK "BUTT_SAVEEND"}     @{"   Quit   " LINK "BUTT_EXIT"}	|
  | ---------------------------------------------------	|
  |                   @{"  Current file   " LINK "BUTT_CURR"}			|
  ·-----------------------------------------------------·



If the pointer remains for a couple of seconds over one button a
short help text will pop up.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "BUTT_LISTVIEW" "List of all definied assigns"

Here you find all added definitions.

In the @{B}first@{UB} column you find the assign-@{" mode " LINK "BUTT_MODUS"}. Single entries may
be moved around the list and placed where ever you want. One click
on an entry makes it the current. A double-click will copy the entry
into the @{" name " LINK "BUTT_ASSIGN"}, @{" path " LINK "BUTT_TO"} und @{" mode " LINK "BUTT_MODUS"} gadgets below the list.

The @{B}second@{UB} column contains the @{" name " LINK "BUTT_ASSIGN"} associated to the @{" path " LINK "BUTT_TO"}
in the @{B}third@{UB} column.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "BUTT_ASSIGN" "Assign name"

Type here the name associated to a @{" path " LINK "BUTT_TO"}.

The name is limited to 31 characters.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "BUTT_TO" "Assign path"

Type here the path associated to a @{" namen " LINK "BUTT_ASSIGN"}.

The path is limited to 127 characters.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "BUTT_MODUS" "Assign mode"
Define the type of assign to be used:

    @{B}Locked@{UB} = Usual method. A path is attached to a name. An old
             definition will be overwritten.

    @{B}Add@{UB}    = Addes a path to an already defined name. With this you
             can read from different paths by using only one single
             name. For example:
                 Assign Locked Test: RAM:
                 Assign Add Test: Work:
                 "Dir Test:" would print all files contained in the
                 drawers @{B}RAM:@{UB} and @{B}Work:@{UB} as if they where all in
                 one single drawer.
             Though, a file would be saved in the drawer that was
             assigned locked.

    @{B}Path@{UB}   = This is a not binding definition, though similar to
             mode @{B}locked@{UB}. A name will be  attached to a path, but
             with every use of that name, the path will be newly
             identified. For example:
             Assign Path FONTS: DF0:FONTS
                 "Dir FONTS:" will print all files in the fonts-
                 drawer of the disk currently in df0: but it will
                 not ask for the initially inserted disk, when the
                 assign was called.

    @{B}Late@{UB}   = Similar to mode @{B}locked@{UB}, but the associated path will be
             evaluated on first use.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "BUTT_DO" "Execute a definition"

A requester opens to choose one from these options:

    @{B}1. Input:@{UB}
	The @{" path " LINK "BUTT_TO"} will be attached to the @{" name " LINK "BUTT_ASSIGN"}
	regarding the assign-@{" mode " LINK "BUTT_MODUS"}.

    @{B}2. All:@{UB}
	The whole list will be executed.

    @{"3. Part" LINK "EXEC_LIST"}

    @{B}4. Abort@{UB}
	Close requester without any further action.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "EXEC_LIST" "Execute partial list"
The execute window has following structure:

  ·-----------------------------------------------------·
  |					| @{"    All     " LINK "EXEC_ALL"}	|
  |					| @{"    Mark    " LINK "EXEC_MARK"}	|
  | @{" List of temporary assigns " LINK "EXEC_TEMP"}		| @{"   Delete   " LINK "EXEC_DEL"}	|
  |					|---------------|
  |					| @{"   Append   " LINK "EXEC_APP"}	|
  |					| @{"    Quit    " LINK "EXEC_DONE"}	|
  ·-----------------------------------------------------·

Drag items from the list in the main window onto this list by mouse.
Proceed as follows:
Click on one item, hold down left mouse button and drag the item off
right or left the listview gadget's boundaries. The item will then
not appear ghosted any more. Now release the left mouse button when
the pointer is over this listview gadget and the item will be added.

Proceed reverse to drag items from this onto the main window's
listview gadget.

@{B}Attention:@{UB} In this procedure no testing will be done to verify
wether an added name has already been definied or not.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "EXEC_TEMP" "List of temporary assigns"

In opposite to the @{" list of all definied assigns " LINK "BUTT_LISTVIEW"} this list,
as you already assumed, is only temporary, so it can not be saved
directly.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "EXEC_ALL" "Execute all temporary assigns"

All in the temporary list definied assigns will be executed one
after another.

Error handling will be done.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "EXEC_MARK" "Execute marked temporary assign"

Only the marked assign will be executed.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "EXEC_DEL" "Delete marked temporary assign"

The mark temporary assign will be removed from the list without
any further request.

(See also @{"delete marked definition" LINK "BUTT_DEL"}.)
@ENDNODE

@NODE "EXEC_APP" "Append temporary assign to main list"

Appends the temporary list to the @{" main list " LINK "BUTT_LISTVIEW"}.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "EXEC_DONE" "Delete temporary assigns"

The temporary list will be removed from memory and the execute
window will be closed.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "BUTT_ADD" "Add current definition to list"

The definitions of @{" name " LINK "BUTT_ASSIGN"}, @{" path " LINK "BUTT_TO"} and @{" mode " LINK "BUTT_MODUS"} will be added
to the list. If the name is already definied, a warning will be
displayed.

In addition, this definition will also be added to the
@{" temporary assign" LINK "EXEC_TEMP"} list automatically. No verifying will be
done, wether the name has already been definied or not.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "BUTT_DEL" "Delete current definition"

The marked @{" definition " LINK "BUTT_LISTVIEW"} will be removed from the list with
a warning.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "BUTT_SAVE" "Save list"

The list will be saved with the @{" current filename " LINK "BUTT_CURR"}. Is the current
filename empty, a file requester will pop up.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "BUTT_SAVEEND" "Save and end"

The list will be saved with the @{" current filename " LINK "BUTT_CURR"} and the
program terminates.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "BUTT_EXIT" "End program"

AssignList will terminate without saving the list. Though, if the
list has been modified a requester will pop up.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "BUTT_CURR" "Current file"

Shows the name, that will be used when the file is saved.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "USE_MENU" "The menu"
The menu-strip contains two items, that will provide you with almost
the same functions as the main window.

@{B}1. Project:@{UB}

    *  @{B}New@{UB}: The list will be deleted. If it has been modified,
         a requester will pop up.

    * @{B}Load@{UB}: Loads a definition file. If the current list has
         been modified, a requester will pop up.

    * @{B}Insert@{UB}: A definition file will be attached to the end of
         the current list. If @{" names " LINK "BUTT_ASSIGN"} where used twice,
         a warning will be displayed.

    * @{" Save " LINK "BUTT_SAVE"}

    * @{B}Save as@{UB}: See @{B}Save@{UB} except, that a file requester will pop up.

    * @{B}About@{UB}: A copyright information will be displayed.

    * @{B}About Project@{UB}: Informations about the current project
         will be displayed.

    * @{B}About MUI@{UB}: An information about @{" MUI " LINK "MUI_README"} will be displayed.

    * @{" Quit " LINK "BUTT_EXIT"}

@{B}2. Options:@{UB}

    * @{B}Create icons@{UB}: Determines wether an icons will be created
         when a file is saved or not. (See also @{"tooltypes" LINK "USE_START"}.)

    * @{B}MUI@{UB}: Starts @{" MUI " LINK "MUI_README"}-preferences.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "FILE_FORMAT" "Definition-file's structure"
A definition file may be as well created using a simple text editor.
Every line must be structured as follows:

A line starts with a key word @{B}locked@{UB}, @{B}add@{UB}, @{B}path@{UB} or @{B}late@{UB}.
(See also @{" assign mode " LINK "BUTT_MODUS"}.)

Then separated by a "," follows the @{" assign name " LINK "BUTT_ASSIGN"} and again
separated by a "," follows the associated @{" path " LINK "BUTT_TO"}.

The line must be ended by a LineFeed (CHR$(10)).

Just print a definition file using for example "type".
@ENDNODE

